<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=12438&amp;p=142304#p142304"><![CDATA[
Well I want to arrange an interview with a NES game designer who worked around 1990 for a professional company.<br />And ask him such questions :<br />How did they make a game for NES back then?<br />What tools they used for making a nes game?<br />What was the progress?<br />How many people worked on a project?<br />What kind of problems did they have?<br />Any good and bad memory from those days?<br />and some other questions which can be added later<br /><br />But I suggest someone with high reputation (maybe an admin or moderator of nesdev) ask such questions from a professional or at least invite him to come and answer the questions.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4330">FARID</a> — Mon Mar 02, 2015 5:20 am</p><hr />
